        "text": ": Yeah. Strict, it means in the sense that making the other responsible. Like an adult has to show teenagers that they will become future responsible adults, too. So they are not just like kids and you just don't say to your kids for example, \"Don't eat this,\" and that's it. If you can just say to your children, \"Don't eat this because you can be sick if you eat too much of this.\" Like you have to give them a reason or you have to make them responsible. They have to understand actually."
