    "speakers": [
      {
        "id": "A",
        "label": "Speaker",
        "voice": "female",
        "accent": "en-US"
      }
    ],
    "transcript": [
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Doron:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "So Pernais, Jamaica's quite a small country, right?"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Pernais:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "It is."
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Doron:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "What's the population?  Not exactly, just"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "more or less"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "."
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Pernais:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "2.7"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "million"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Doron:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Okay, that's pretty small.  Do you have a problem with people leaving, like for university or of to get better jobs going to other countries?"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Pernais:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Yes, a lot of people leave, but I don't know if it's so much a problem because Jamaicans have been"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "migrating"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "for decades now.  A lot of people don't know that half of the Jamaican population actually lives outside of Jamaica."
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Doron:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Half?"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Pernais:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Yes."
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Doron:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "So that means there's like 5.4 million Jamaicans?"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Pernais:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Yes."
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Doron:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "And only half of them live in Jamaica?"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Pernais:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Yes.  Possibly."
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Doron:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Where do they usually go?"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Pernais:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Most Jamaicans that migrate go to America."
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Doron:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "'Cause it's so close."
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Pernais:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Yes.  And because they have family members there.  Maybe.  And other people go to Canada and the U.K., for example."
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Doron:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Do you get a lot of"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "immigration"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "?  Do you get many people moving to Jamaica to live from other places?"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Pernais:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Recently, there has been an increase in that.  People coming from other Caribbean islands, especially with the situation, the economic situation in Haiti these days.  A lot of Haitians actually come over to Jamaica to find work, and, you know, to...  just to, just"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "for a better life"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": ", really."
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Doron:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Is it very close?"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Pernais:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "It is very close.  It is quite close."
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Doron:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "How do they usually get to Jamaica?"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Pernais:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "By boat."
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Doron:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "So..."
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Pernais:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Which is quite dangerous, but..."
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Doron:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Yeah, I hear a lot of it in history the last couple of decades of"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "boat people"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": ", right?  But you don't often hear about Haitian boat people.  Usually people getting in boats and trying to get to the States, right?"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Pernais:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Yes.  But I guess Jamaica's closer, so they"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "go for"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Jamaica."
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Doron:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Yeah. What kind of jobs do people"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "go for"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "when they get to Jamaica?"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Pernais:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Well, a lot of them"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "end up"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "working in bars and restaurants, and... yeah, just jobs like that."
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Doron:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "I guess there's a lot of tourists in Jamaica?"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Pernais:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "There are quite a lot of tourists."
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Doron:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "So there must be a lot of jobs in the tourism industry."
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Pernais:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Yes.  Always."
      }
    ],
