    "transcript": [
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Todd:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "So, Julia, we're both teachers."
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Julia:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "That's right."
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Todd:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "And are you familier with the different learner types?"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Julia:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "A little bit, yes, I"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "encounter"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "different kinds of learners in my classrooms."
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Todd:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "OK, so for example, what kind of learner are you?"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Julia:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "I think possibly more than one, maybe overlap on a couple, but"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "primarily"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "a visual learner so I'd have to take it in through my eyes usually like with a picture.  I certainly have to see a word if I'm learning a language. I have to see it written down."
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Todd:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "So you need a"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "phonetic"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "script"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "?  You need something?"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Julia:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "I need something visual."
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Todd:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Yeah for it to stick in your head?"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Julia:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "For it to stay in my mind, it has to have a visual.  I can't just hear it for example.  I can't just hear a word and remember it.  I have to have some sort of visual to connect it to."
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Todd:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "OK, so you're a"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "visual learner"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": ", anything else?"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Julia:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "I think it's called a visual learner.  I don't know the technical term for it but an emotional learner if a..."
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Todd:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Really?"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Julia:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Yeah.  If a piece of information or the thing that I'm learning is attached to an emotional experience, I store it very definitively.  I can remember it.  I can"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "recall"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "it.  If it's just a neutral, say a sentence, I can't remember it.  It has to have a back story.  It has to have an emotional connection somehow."
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Todd:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Right.  It has to have some connection?"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Julia:"
      },
      {
        "speaker": "A",
        "text": "Yes, yeah. Usually a personal story especially humor.  If there's a joke involved, if it made me laugh at the time of learning it.  I'm a laughter learner, I don't know if that's a real one but definitely an emotional response makes it much more easy for me to learn something."
      }
    ],
