        "text": "Is it now? I think that once you have the skill set, then you'll know how to work along with the water and work along with the air, if you're diving for instance. But without those skills, I would like to keep my feet firmly planted on the floor, thank you very much, on the ground, thank you very much. We are in the full swing of spring. The phrase âfull swingâ means at its highest level. Notice the following: I prefer the beach, to be honest. The phrase âto be honestâ is used when telling someone what you genuinely think. Notice the following: Iâm good with that. I like the sand, waves, everything.  Iâm so good with that. The phrase âIâm good with thatâ is used to say you are happy with what is happening. Notice the following: I guess the lakes can count as a beach. The phrase âcount asâ is used to say that one thing is thought to be the same as another particular thing. Notice the following: I donât think I could swim to save my life. The phrase âto save my lifeâ means it is impossible for you to do something. Notice the following: I donât even know if I could keep myself up afloat anymore. The phrase âkeep myself afloatâ means you can stay above the water. Notice the following:"
